California as an island with indented northern coast and blank to its north.
Dedicated to Thomas Treyor with coat of arms above. (upper left).

Issued in: Geographia Emendata & Locupletata, Editio quarta, Pag[e]: 38 /Dionysius Periegetes, 1704, which contains world map showing California as an island. Text in Greek and Latin; contains 16 copper-engraved maps. Reissued in 1718 (Editio tertia) and in 1726 (Editio quarta; with Typis Guil. Bowyer).
